(!begin_liste) [Availability]

!item [Name:]
ØGraphics handleÆ - Obtain ID of the (!nolink [VDI]) workstation.

!item [Opcode:]
77

!item [Syntax:]
int16_t graf_xhandle ( int16_t *gr_hwchar, int16_t *gr_hhchar, int16_t *gr_hwbox,
                   int16_t *gr_hhbox,  int16_t *device );

!item [Description:]
The call graf_xhandle obtains the ID of the screen workstation to which the
(!nolink [AES]) outputs. The following apply:

!begin_xlist !short [Parameter]
!item [Parameter]
Meaning
!item [~]
~
!item [gr_hwchar]
Width, (!U)and(!u)
!item [gr_hhchar]
Height of a character from the system font, in points
!item [gr_hwbox]
Width, (!U)and(!u)
!item [gr_hhbox]
Height of a cell into which any character from the system font fits completely

!item [device] Workstation handle of the (!nolink [AES]) (vdi_device)

!end_xlist

(!B)Note:(!b) The information from the parameters (!I)gr_hwbox(!i) or
(!I)gr_hhbox(!i) is used be the (!nolink [AES]) for the width of the
individual window components.

!item [(!nolink [Return]) value:]
The function returns the ID (handle) of the opened (!nolink [VDI]) workstation.

!item [Availability:]
Since KAOS 1.4

!item [Group:]
Graphics library

